{"serial": "39008", "department_serial": 37, "code": "MS5049", "class": "*", "name": {"en": "Theory and Technology of energy storage", "ch": "儲能原理與技術"}, "notice": {"en": "", "ch": ""}, "instructor": {"en": ["Hung, Wei-Hsuan"], "ch": ["洪緯璿"]}, "credits": 3, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 2, "session": ["2", "3", "4"]}, "loc": {"building": "E6", "room": "B142"}}], "isRequired": false, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": -1, "department": {"ch": "材料科學與工程研究所碩士班", "en": "Institute of Materials Science and Engineering"}, "system": {"ch": "碩博同修", "en": "Master/Doctoral Programme"}, "language": {"ch": "英語", "en": "English"}, "card": {"ch": "不使用", "en": "None"}, "assigned": 1, "selected": 60, "remark": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "goal": {"ch": "能源消耗是21世紀的重要挑戰之一，我們正在尋找有效和可持續的方法來儲存這些能源供需求使用。此外，當越來越多的能源使用風能和太陽能等波動性可再生能源生產時，儲能將具有重大意義。隨著能源需求的變化和技術的進步，儲能領域不斷發展、適應和創新。為儲能開發了幾種不同的儲能方法，例如電池/超級電容器：一系列電化學存儲解決方案，包括先進的化學電池、流動電池和電容器。熱：捕獲熱量和冷度，按需產生能量或抵消能源需求。機械存儲：利用動能或引力能存儲電力的其他創新技術。氫燃料儲存：多餘的發電可以通過電解轉化為氫氣。", "en": "Energy consumption is one of the important challenges of the 21st century, we are looking for effective and sustainable methods to store that energy for use on demand. Also, energy storage will be of major importance when more and more energy is produced using fluctuating renewable sources like wind and solar power. The energy storage field has continued to evolve, adapt, and innovate in response to changing energy requirements and advances in technology. Several different energy storage methods are developed for energy storage, for example Batteries/Supercapacitor: a range of electrochemical storage solutions, including advanced chemistry batteries, flow batteries, and capacitors. Thermal: capturing heat and cold to create energy on demand or offset energy needs. Mechanical Storage: other innovative technologies to harness kinetic or gravitational energy to store electricity. Hydrogen fuel storage: excess electricity generation can be converted into hydrogen via electrolysis."}, "outline": {"ch": "1.可再生能源與儲能的介紹\n-化石燃料；機械存儲；電氣/電磁存儲；電化學儲能；熱能存儲；氫燃料儲存\n2.電化學儲能的基本原理\n-如何通過電化學反應存儲和釋放能量？\n-通過電化學反應操作的儲能裝置\n-EES應用的關鍵組件和材料\n3.儲能係統中的電荷轉移過程\n-將電荷存儲在傳統電池中之原理\n-將電荷存儲在可充電電池中之原理\n-固體電極材料/液體電解質/固體電解質中的電荷轉移\n4.在可充電電池中使用奈米結構和奈米材料的基礎知識\n- 奈米效應對可充電電池的總體存儲性能的影響\n- 奈米效應對電解質|電解質界面的電荷轉移之探討\n- 奈米結構電極材料的設計原理\n-電池中傳統奈米結構和奈米材料的介紹，包括合成和製造方法\n-用於儲能裝置的石墨烯之應用\n5.關於氫能存儲的基礎知識\n-氫能的發展與重要性\n-氫能儲氫材料及其工作原理\n-傳統材料和奈米材料中的氫儲技術", "en": "1.Introduction of Renewable Energy\n-Fossil Fuel; Mechanical Storage; Electrical/Electromagnetic Storage; Electrochemical Energy Storage; Thermal Energy Storage; Hydrogen fuel storage\n2.Fundamentals About Electrochemical Energy Storage\n-How Is Energy Stored and Released Through Electrochemical Reactions?\n-Energy Storage Devices Operated by Electrochemical Reactions\n-Key Components and Materials for EES Application\n3.Charges Transfer Process in Energy Storage System\n- Storage of Charges in a Primary Cell\n-Storage of Charges in a Rechargeable Cell\n-Transfer of Charges in Solid Electrode Material/a Liquid Electrolyte/a Solid Electrolyte\n4.Fundamentals About Use of Nanostructures and Nanomaterials in a Rechargeable Cell\n-“Nano” Effect on the General Storage Properties of a Rechargeable Cell\n-“Nano” Effect on the Charge Transfer Across Electrode|Electrolyte Interface\n-Design Principles for “Kinetically Stable” Nanostructured Electrode Materials\n-Introduction of Traditional Nanostructures and Nanomaterials in Batteries including Synthesis and Fabrication Methods\n-Graphene for Soft Energy Storage Devices\n5.Fundamentals About Hydrogen Energy Storage\n-The Significance of Hydrogen Energy .\n-Hydrogen Energy and Hydrogen Storage Materials and its working principle\n-Hydrogen in Traditional Material and Nanomaterial"}, "textbook": {"ch": "-Guo, Yu-Guo_ Nanostructures and Nanomaterials for Batteries (ISBN 978-981-13-6233-0)\n-Xin, Gongbiao _ Gaseous and Electrochemical Hydrogen Storage Properties of Mg-Based Thin Films (ISBN 978-3-662-49404-2)", "en": "-Guo, Yu-Guo_ Nanostructures and Nanomaterials for Batteries (ISBN 978-981-13-6233-0)\n-Xin, Gongbiao _ Gaseous and Electrochemical Hydrogen Storage Properties of Mg-Based Thin Films (ISBN 978-3-662-49404-2)"}, "selfCompiledRate": {"ch": "40", "en": "40"}, "instructMethod": {"ch": "講授\n研討", "en": ["Lecture", "Seminar"]}, "gradMethod": {"ch": "出席　Attendance 10％  期中報告(I) Midterm: 30％\n期中報告(II) Midterm: 30％  期末報告 Final: 30％\nTOTAL: 100％", "en": "出席　Attendance 10％  期中報告(I) Midterm: 30％\n期中報告(II) Midterm: 30％  期末報告 Final: 30％\nTOTAL: 100％"}, "officeHour": {"ch": "Wednesday 1pm to 2pm", "en": "Wednesday 1pm to 2pm"}, "teachWeeks": {"ch": "18", "en": "18"}, "flexDiscription": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "domain": {"ch": "材料科學基礎課程\n\n\n、\n\n\n材料科學專業課程", "en": "材料科學基礎課程\n\n\n、\n\n\n材料科學專業課程"}, "map": {"ch": [{"competencies": "專業知識", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["口頭報告/口試", "出席/課堂表現"]}, {"competencies": "邏輯推理", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["口頭報告/口試", "出席/課堂表現"]}, {"competencies": "論文撰寫能力", "rating": "(3)普通", "assesments": ["口頭報告/口試", "出席/課堂表現"]}, {"competencies": "國際合作", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["口頭報告/口試", "自我評量/同儕互評"]}, {"competencies": "國際視野", "rating": "(3)普通", "assesments": ["口頭報告/口試", "自我評量/同儕互評"]}, {"competencies": "終身學習", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["口頭報告/口試", "出席/課堂表現", "作品/創作展演"]}], "en": [{"competencies": "Basic Knowledge", "rating": "(4)High", "assesments": ["Presentation/Oral Exam", "Attendance/Performance"]}, {"competencies": "Logic and analytic ability", "rating": "(4)High", "assesments": ["Presentation/Oral Exam", "Attendance/Performance"]}, {"competencies": "Thesis - writing ability", "rating": "(3)Medium", "assesments": ["Presentation/Oral Exam", "Attendance/Performance"]}, {"competencies": "Team work ability", "rating": "(4)High", "assesments": ["Presentation/Oral Exam", "Self Assessment/ Peer Assessment"]}, {"competencies": "Global perspective", "rating": "(3)Medium", "assesments": ["Presentation/Oral Exam", "Self Assessment/ Peer Assessment"]}, {"